<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-126] Start sequence is incorrect</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-126</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It should be noted that this sequence is only critical during the first (initial) startup. After that it doesn&apos;t matter so much because all services have correctly registered and have been cataloged.&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hi Yes,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for finding this Alex. The manual should be updated with the&lt;br/&gt;
correct order.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-cf&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;On 03/07/2013 09:39 AM, Alex Kulyavtsev wrote:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; Hi Colin.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; This is not what the manual says.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; Shall it be corrected then? Or, add description for startup sequence&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; in different situations (first start, restart).&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; The manual (or online information) does not describe graceful shutdown&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; sequence for separate MGS/MDT configuration, it will be nice to add&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; that too.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; Alex.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; E.g.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.lustre.org/manual/LustreManual20_HTML/LustreOperations.html#5&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.lustre.org/manual/LustreManual20_HTML/LustreOperations.html#5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
